.\" ecr_lambda_update(1) -- ECR Image Push and Lambda Update Script
.SH NAME
ecr_lambda_update \- automate Docker image push to ECR and Lambda update
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ecr_lambda_update
[\-r \fIREPO_NAME\fP]
[\-l \fILAMBDA_NAME\fP]
[\-i \fIIMAGE_NAME\fP]
[\-g \fIAWS_REGION\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This script automates the process of pushing a Docker image to Amazon Elastic Container Registry (ECR) and updating an AWS Lambda function with the latest image.
.PP
.B ecr_lambda_update
accepts the following options:
.TP
.B \-r \fIREPO_NAME\fP
Specify the ECR repository name.
.TP
.B \-l \fILAMBDA_NAME\fP
Specify the Lambda function name.
.TP
.B \-i \fIIMAGE_NAME\fP
(Optional) Specify a custom Docker image name (defaults to "latest").
.TP
.B \-g \fIAWS_REGION\fP
(Optional) Specify the AWS region (defaults to "us-west-2").
.SH EXAMPLES
To push a Docker image to ECR and update a Lambda function:
.B ecr_lambda_update -r my-ecr-repo -l my-lambda-function -i custom-image -g us-east-1
